other_tests.findings: The liver is diffusely echogenic consistent with fatty deposition. An echogenic lesion without internal vascularity in segment VII of the liver is a hemangioma. The gallbladder is incompletely distended with gallstones, wall edema, and a small amount of pericholecystic fluid. Sonographic ___ sign is positive. The common duct is not dilated measuring 6 mm. Assessment of the pancreas is limited due to overlying bowel gas. Limited views of the right kidney are normal. The spleen is normal, measuring 11.8 cm.
